				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">It really is next to impossible to please some people.  Sounds to me like Ryan is doing more to help our class and game balance overall than any other developer before him.  The fact that he is already looking into many of the problems that we have agreed on as a majority is promising.
<br />

<br />
I'm sorry to those who are upset because the new pet is going to help out raiding mages.  Do you somehow think that it's going to be detrimental to non-raiding mages?  No offense, but that is where most of the help is needed.  Also, reread the post.  There are many things in there that will help the mage overall having nothing to do with raids.
<br />

<br />
Where do non-raiding mages have an advantage?  AA's pure and simple.  Many people spend all of their online time in raids or waiting for a raid to start leaving little time to acquire xp.  That's the tradeoff and a decision that you make on how to spend you time.  They both have positive's and negatives.
<br />

<br />
I suggest if you want to be God's in a game you should try single player RPG's as MMO's are not for you.  
<br />

<br />
