				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I can't speak for GoD, but our existing pet runes seem to be keeping the pet alive in almost all fights in PoP raids bar Quarm...but MSIV is a GoD spell and GOD raids probably require that so lets see.
<br />

<br />
The majority of the posts I'm seeing in the class balance forum are 1) to do with comparative pet surviveability against exp type mobs in group/solo situations and 2) how little utilty/defense we have compared to most other dps classes that surpass us in dps, ie, why are we giving up so much defense/utility to come in behind on offense?
<br />

<br />
Ryan's answers do little to address these points (but he does touch on it! yay), and I'm upset that he thinks that focus items are the way to go for everyone, unless the focus items are as easy to get as the DPoC. Historically the focus items have been very difficult to obtain, which worries me--as its not so difficult to run into problems with our pets surviving.  I'd more like to see an across the board increase in base pets, with existing focus items also being boosted and more pet help AAs JUST FOR MAGES.
<br />

<br />
Also, why no discussion on our craptacular pet heal ratio/recast times. (Except for the discussion on mend companion, excellent news there!)
<br />

<br />
Thanks for posting this.  He should have come here directly but at least he's talking to Jaytee! 
